description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and organised Administration Assistant to join our Recruitment Team based within Human Resources Department at 2 Kings Court, Worcester.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Recruitment Team is responsible for the end to end recruitment process of all staff joining the Trust, looking after a wide variety of clinical and non- clinical vacancies.  We ensure that all new employees have a smooth transition into post and that they are compliant with the national NHS standards required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working alongside the Senior HR Manager and Team Leader you will be responsible for the production of contracts of employment and associated documents, and providing administration support for ongoing recruitment project work.   The role will also support the rest of the Recruitment team in various aspects of the recruitment process.  Therefore need a flexible working attitude with the ability to prioritise your workload.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should have recent, relevant experience in an administrative/secretarial/reception role with a working knowledge of Microsoft Office - Word, Excel, Outlook and have a Level 2 qualification in a Business Administration related subject, for example: NVQ, OCR/RSA, City &amp; Guilds, GCSE (Grade A-C).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a supportive team and you will receive full training to ensure you can succeed in this role.  This is a new post within the team and initially advertised on a fixed term contract for 12 months.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Shortlisted candidates will be required to undertake an additional assessment as part of the selection process and this will be conducted via email prior to the interview.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Lucy Muller, Senior HR Manager – Recruitment Services on 07714 486530 or email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;lucy.muller@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews:  Thursday, 26&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
